#: resources/views/page/sections/data-export.phtml:9
msgid "webtrees protects data inside the application by using privacy rules, access rights, and role-dependent visibility."
msgstr ""

#: resources/views/page/sections/data-export.phtml:10
msgid "When data is exported, copied, printed, saved as a file, or captured as a screenshot, the technical protection mechanisms of webtrees no longer apply to that exported copy."
msgstr ""

#: resources/views/page/sections/data-export.phtml:11
msgid "Users who export or otherwise take data out of webtrees are responsible for handling that copy lawfully and with appropriate care."
msgstr ""

#: resources/views/page/sections/data-export.phtml:15
msgid "There are several ways in which data can leave webtrees:"
msgstr ""

#: resources/views/page/sections/data-export.phtml:20
msgid "GEDCOM export can export genealogical data from a tree."
msgstr ""

#: resources/views/page/sections/data-export.phtml:21
msgid "Depending on the export function and its settings, the export can be created with different webtrees privacy levels or role-based views, for example without privacy filtering, as visible to managers, as visible to members, or as visible to visitors."
msgstr ""

#: resources/views/page/sections/data-export.phtml:22
msgid "An export without privacy filtering can contain all data, including confidential or otherwise protected information in plain text."
msgstr ""

#: resources/views/page/sections/data-export.phtml:25
msgid "Reports can extract selected parts of the data from webtrees as text or generated output."
msgstr ""

#: resources/views/page/sections/data-export.phtml:26
msgid "Reports are generated according to the webtrees protection and visibility settings that apply to the user creating the report."
msgstr ""

#: resources/views/page/sections/data-export.phtml:29
msgid "Screenshots can capture the information that is visible on screen."
msgstr ""

#: resources/views/page/sections/data-export.phtml:30
msgid "The displayed page is still controlled by the webtrees protection settings, but the screenshot itself is no longer controlled by webtrees after it has been created."
msgstr ""

#: resources/views/page/sections/data-export.phtml:35
msgid "Export functions and report access should therefore be granted only to users who may handle the exported data responsibly."
msgstr ""

#: resources/views/page/sections/data-export.phtml:36
msgid "Before exported data is passed on or published elsewhere, it should be checked again for living persons, confidential facts, media files, and other protected content."
msgstr ""

#: resources/views/page/sections/further-information.phtml:24
msgid "Version checks"
msgstr ""

#: resources/views/page/sections/further-information.phtml:27
msgid "webtrees can check whether a newer webtrees version is available."
msgstr ""

#: resources/views/page/sections/further-information.phtml:28
#, php-format
msgid "For this purpose, the webtrees server sends a request to %s."
msgstr ""

#: resources/views/page/sections/further-information.phtml:29
msgid "The request contains the installed webtrees version, the PHP version, a site identifier generated by webtrees, and the database driver used."
msgstr ""

#: resources/views/page/sections/further-information.phtml:30
msgid "The server receiving the request may also process normal technical request metadata, such as the IP address of this web server, the time of the request, and HTTP headers."
msgstr ""

#: resources/views/page/sections/further-information.phtml:31
msgid "webtrees stores the result locally and normally performs this check at most once per day; an administrator can also start a manual check in the control panel."
msgstr ""

#: resources/views/page/sections/further-information.phtml:32
msgid "The check is performed by the webtrees server, not by the visitor browser."
msgstr ""

#: resources/views/page/sections/further-information.phtml:33
msgid "This module does not provide a separate setting to disable the webtrees core version check; preventing it would require a webtrees or server configuration change."
msgstr ""

#: resources/views/page/sections/further-information.phtml:37
msgid "Custom modules can provide their own latest-version URL."
msgstr ""

#: resources/views/page/sections/further-information.phtml:38
msgid "When the webtrees control panel is opened, webtrees may request these URLs to compare the installed module version with the latest version offered by the module author."
msgstr ""

#: resources/views/page/sections/further-information.phtml:39
#, php-format
msgid "For this module, the latest-version URL is hosted on GitHub at %s."
msgstr ""

#: resources/views/page/sections/further-information.phtml:40
msgid "This request may transmit the IP address of this web server and normal technical request metadata to GitHub."
msgstr ""

#: resources/views/page/sections/further-information.phtml:41
msgid "The result is cached locally for up to one day."
msgstr ""

#: resources/views/page/sections/further-information.phtml:42
msgid "Administrators can prevent module version checks by using modules that do not provide a latest-version URL or by adapting the module code accordingly."
msgstr ""
